column5: https://www.theweathernetwork.com/videos/Gallery/salmon-dodge-traffic-to-cross-washed-out-road/sharevideo/5236014612001  Ever ran over a fish with your truck?
LOL, I have never seen a caution salmon crossing sign!
Thats gnarly!!!!  Where there is a will....  How cool would it be to witness that in person!
To answer the question: to get to the "sp--m bank".

I saw something similar back in the late 80's when they still stocked salmon in lake Erie. If you are familiar with Youngs Creek , Norfolk County, there is a dam and a parking lot at the town of Vittoria. There had been a lot of rain one fall we figured everything else would be blown, it takes a lot of rain to blow Youngs with the sandy soil so we drove down , much to our surprise the parking lot had six inches of water in it and the crazy Cohos were trying to make redds in the gravel.
